\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. S. pinnata} (Lam.) O. Kuntze,{\i  Revis. Gen.}{\b  3}: 170 (1898). Erect, freely branched annual 25-75 cm, appressed-pubescent at least above. Leaves 1- to 2-pinnatisect, with linear segments. Capitula very numerous, in a more or less corymbose panicle. Involucre 5-6 × 3-4 mm, obconical, with 2 linear bracts at its base; involucral bracts purplish with yellow scarious margin in fruit. Ligule c. 1·5 mm, yellow. Achenes attenuate below, appressed-pubescent. Pappus-scales alternately acuminate-aristate and obtuse.{\i  Cultivated or disturbed ground. Naturalized in E. Spain; an occasional casual elsewhere.} [Hs.] ({\i South America}.)
\par

