\pard\f0\fs24\qc By A. Hansen.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals or short-lived perennials. Leaves entire or pinnatifid, alternate. Capitula large. Involucral bracts in 2-3 rows. Receptacle convex-subglobose, with numerous scales or setae. Outer florets ligulate, usually female; inner florets tubular, hermaphrodite. Achenes obovoid, usually covered by a basal tuft of long hairs. Pappus of 5-10 long-awned scales.
