\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. T. minuta} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 887 (1753). Erect, glabrous, strong smelling annual up to 100 cm, with short branches. Leaves 3-15 × 3-10 cm, pinnatisect; segments 3-7, 2-8 × 0·2-0·6 cm, linear-lanceolate; only the lower leaves opposite. Capitula numerous in dense terminal corymbs. Involucre 8-12 × 1·5-2 mm, cylindrical, of 3-4 yellowish-green bracts. Ligules usually 1-3 mm, obovate-spathulate, yellowish-green. Tubular florets 4-5, 3-4 mm, green. Achenes 4-6 × 0·5-1 mm, linear, black, with appressed white hairs. Pappus of 5 scales 0·5-3 mm.{\i  Waste places and cultivated ground. Locally naturalized in S. Europe, casual elsewhere.} [Ga It Ju.] ({\i South America}.)
