\pard\f0\fs28 Leaves alternate, very rarely opposite, simple or pinnatisect. Capitula with or without ligules; outer florets usually female or sterile, the inner hermaphrodite or functionally male; corolla usually white or yellow. Receptacle with or without scales. Anthers usually obtuse at base. Style-branches truncate and papillose at apex. Pappus absent or a corona or auricle.
